To setup the Engine in pycharm please use the pycharm VCS control integration https://www.jetbrains.com/help/pycharm/manage-projects-hosted-on-github.html#share-on-GitHub
  1. Login to Github and add your account to PyCharm
  2. Through VCS card select Get from Version Control
  3. select Github and the Repository zigcloud/Engine
  4. PyCharm will automatically create venv and install all packages based on the requirements.txt file

To setup the Engine manually you need Git
  1. Basic commands and installation for Git https://education.github.com/git-cheat-sheet-education.pdf
  2. Create empty folder and clone the zigcloud/Engine using git commands
  3. Optional: Create virtual environment
  4. using the selected Python environment enabled install the site packages using the requirements.txt file -> pip install -r requirements.txt
